1. **Lažna** vest se brzo širila društvenim mrežama. (False news spread quickly on social media.)
2. Ona je bila *lažna* prijateljica koja me je izdala kada mi je bila najpotrebnija. (She was a fake friend who betrayed me when I needed her the most.)
3. Učenik je dobio *lažnu* ocenu zato što nije predao domaći zadatak na vreme. (The student received a false grade because he did not submit the homework on time.)
4. Ona je rekla da ima *lažne* zube, ali ja to nikada ne bih pogodila. (She said she had false teeth, but I would have never guessed.)
5. Prevarant je koristio *lažnu* identifikaciju kako bi dobio pristup osetljivim informacijama. (The fraudster used a false identification to gain access to sensitive information.)
6. Njegov *lažni* osmeh je bio lako uočljiv i nije uspevao da sakrije svoje pravo raspoloženje. (His fake smile was easily noticeable and failed to conceal his true mood.)
7. Kompanija je optužena za prodaju *lažnih* proizvoda koji su bili lošeg kvaliteta. (The company was accused of selling false products that were of poor quality.)
8. Sve *lažnije* vesti o globalnom zagrevanju izazivaju zabrinutost među naučnicima. (Increasingly false news about global warming is causing concern among scientists.)
9. Mlada pevačica je bila u centru skandala kada su se pojavile *lažne* fotografije na kojima se navodno nalazi gola. (The young singer was at the center of a scandal when false photos allegedly showing her naked appeared.)
10. Njihova *lažna* obećanja su nas navele da im damo šansu, ali na kraju su nas izneverili. (Their false promises convinced us to give them a chance, but in the end, they let us down.)